<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-2570] CQL: incorrect error message running truncate on CF that does not exist</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-2570</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Run truncate on a CF that does not exist. The error message is misleading.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;CQLSH&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;cqlsh&amp;gt; truncate aaaa;
Unable to complete request: one or more nodes were unavailable.
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;cassandra-cli&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;[&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;default&lt;/span&gt;@cqldb] truncate aaaaaaaaa;
aaaaaaaaa not found in current keyspace.
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
